## Lecture 8: github.com training

* Create a github account at [https://github.com/signup](https://github.com/signup)
* The login using your new account

### Organizations

* Create an organization: `training-org-2026-yourname` where yourname is something unique like "qknight"

### We make a PR

* fork <https://github.com/nixcloud/git-training> into your organization
* clone git-training to your local computer
* create a branch "new_chick" from branch "main"
* Add a 🐔 to the README.md and commit your change
* Then push the branch "new_chick" to your forked git-training repository
* Visit https://github.com/training-org-2026-yourname/git-training and do a PR to https://github.com/nixcloud/git-training

### We create an issue

<https://github.com/nixcloud/git-training/issues> is currently empty but we need to create a "Cucco storm"! 

* **Create an issue** with proper markdown and ask for some ultra-stupid request, feel free to use your 'AI slop' generator of choice.
* Wait for upstream to react to your request

## Lecture 9: azure devops training

* There are **no ego-centric namespaces like github.com/qknight** nor are there organizations
* All we are left with is git repositories and branches
* As a consequence, PRs look very differently

So do this:

* create an empty repository
* push the git-trainig repository there
* create a branch `branchibranch` and do a PR, as a reviewer set someone from your team

